                        "id": "d234f36d-3302-4441-989c-7101cc8a7fd8",
                        "exerciseName": "Neck front",
                        "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Complex of neck exercises. 1. Front</strong></p><p>Exercise on the front of your neck.</p><p>Essential basic technique for your healthy neck!</p><p>- The neck gets longer and stronger;</p><p>- Mobility of the head increases;</p><p>- Tension is released;</p><p>- The front part of the neck is prepared for special techniques on the double chin zone;</p><p>- Indispensable preparation for the all next exercises.</p><p><strong>Caution:&nbsp;</strong>As with all neck exercises, perform it very slowly and gently! If you do it correctly, you will feel comfortable at any time while exercising.</p><p>In this business, it is better to do it softly rather than zealously.</p><p>Breathe smoothly during any exercise. It is crucial for the result.</p><p><strong>Technique</strong></p><p><strong>1 Action</strong>. Hands up, chin down</p><p>- Stand in the upright position with the crown pointed upward.</p><p>- Put your hands up and hold your elbows with the hands over your head, tilt your head forward with slight pressure. There could be some soft tissues between your chin and your chest, it is normal. If there&rsquo;s any, just press it with your chin.&nbsp;</p><p>- Keep pressing your chin slightly to the chest for the next 4 inhale-exhale rounds.</p><p>- Breathe evenly.</p><p>- After breathing out for the 4<sup>th</sup> time, start moving your chin up, drop your hands down and relax.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>2 Action</strong>. Stretching</p><p>- straighten the chin slowly further up, feel the stretching in the front part of the neck, keep this position for the next 4 inhale-exhale rounds.</p><p>Repeat it one more time, if you feel like it.</p><p><strong>Attention!&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Do not let your head drop backwards completely when you bend the back of your neck backwards too. This is a mistake. This mistake can cost you possible pain and a lumbago, so please keep the back of your neck as elongated as it could be while stretching the chin upwards.</p><p><br></p><p>After stretching the front of your neck, be sure to do the exercise for the back of the neck also.</p><p><em>Take it easy!&nbsp;</em><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f609.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
