                        "id": "34728d3f-c5d7-4804-87a7-0ab679814f1e",
                        "exerciseName": "Mobilization of the forehead",
                        "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Soft-tissues mobilization of the forehead and smoothing the forehead</strong></p><p><strong>Caution:</strong> Please do all the face massage techniques <strong>with the&nbsp;</strong><strong>power a one-year old baby</strong> could exert. Apply this rule to all the pressings, folding and frictions.</p><p>This technique is super effective! So, don&rsquo;t get carried away!&nbsp;</p><p>If you do this exercise for the first time, do it half-heartedly.&nbsp;</p><p>In this business, it is better to practice a little but regularly rather than a lot at once.</p><p>Check out what muscles you will work on</p><p><span class=\"fr-video fr-deletable fr-fvc fr-dvb fr-draggable\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"true\"><iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/543723284\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\" class=\"fr-draggable\"></iframe></span><br></p><p>Benefits<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; Mobility of soft tissues of the forehead increases;<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; Skins metabolism improves;<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; Clogged lymph starts moving and removes the cellular waste;<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; The forehead is revitalized;<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; Horizontal lines on your forehead are getting smoother;<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; Eyebrows are lifted up;<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; Forehead hairline is better supplied with blood, which means better hair growth in the long-term.</p><p><strong>Technique</strong><br>- Clean your face and hands, as always before you start any massage technique.<br>- Place your elbows on the table, use the both hands.<br>- Place your fingertips on your eyebrows, press them slightly to the eyebrow bones and hold for 2 to 3 seconds, then slide your fingertips with all the soft tissues slowly towards the top of your head, stay in this position for 5 to 6 seconds and feel the tension you created.<br>- Relax the back of your neck, let your head rest on the fingertips.<br>- Keep the same pressure and start moving your fingertips together to the left and then slowly to the right, keep them moving horizontally through the soft tissues from the left to the right and back with the same pressure. Use the weight of your head to slide your fingertips little by little up to the hairline and a bit further through the hair.<br>- If you found a spot on your forehead that feels especially cramped and tensed - pay more attention to this spot but don&rsquo;t overdo it. <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f609.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; It is better to come back to it the next day.<br>- Finish the left and right movements on the hairline, then return the fingertips to the eyebrows, but this time place the both hands on the left side of your forehead, so that the index finger of your right hand would be between the eyebrows.<br>- Press it for 2 seconds, move the soft tissues upwards, then stop for 5 seconds to feel your soft tissues, make the left-to-right movements with your fingertips, let them the reach the hairline and go a little bit further through your hair under the weight of your head.</p><p>- Repeat the sequence on the right side.</p><p>- If your skin is in a good shape, the soft tissues will move freely through the left-to-right movements leaving pleasant sensations.</p><p><strong>Attention!</strong><br>Please do all the face massage techniques with the power a one-year old baby could exert. Apply this rule to all the pressings, folding and frictions.</p><p>If you do this exercise for the first time, the sensations may be different from person to person.&nbsp;</p><p>The good news is, it is hard to harm yourself using this technique. <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f642.svg);\">&nbsp;</span><br>Try it and feel how your soft tissues respond!</p><p><br></p><p><em>Good luck! <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60c.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</em></p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\"> <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"\"></a></p>",
