                        "id": "c4af1790-2787-411e-a77f-50cff124d37f",
                        "exerciseName": "Relaxation F2",
                        "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Massage of the muscle that lifts the upper lip. F2</strong></p><p>Now let&#39;s work on the F2 levator muscles.<br>The muscle that lifts the upper lip (F2) tenses when you doubt something very much or hear, for example, blatant lies))). Many people in this case skeptically raise their upper lip and cheek, they say: &ldquo;Well, well, come on, tell me! &quot; And these muscles are also involved in our big smile, they work when we chew or brush our teeth. They work constantly, which means they constantly accumulate residual spasm.<br>Because of this spasm, ugly nasolabial folds are formed, the lower eyelid sags, ugly plump ridges are outlined under the cheekbones, and lymph stagnation at the site of the spasm leads to enlarged pores and bumpy skin on these ridges.<br>This simple technique will help you get rid of annoying imperfections!</p><p><span class=\"fr-video fr-deletable fr-fvc fr-dvb fr-draggable\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"true\"><iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/608061753\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\" class=\"fr-draggable\"></iframe></span><br></p><p><strong>Technique:</strong><br><strong>1 step</strong>. Compression.<br>We put our fingers on the attachment points of this muscle: the upper one is in the area of the center of the eye socket under the eye, the lower one is a fingertip away from the wing of the nose. We press with the fingertips deep into the muscle itself. Then hold pressure for 5 seconds, and then we move our fingers together and collect the fold. Hold it for 20 seconds or 4 inhale-exhale rounds. This extra tension will signal to the brain that the muscle needs to be completely relaxed.<br>Let it go.</p><p><strong>2 step</strong>. Stretching.<br>Now we reposition the fingertips in the middle of the muscle, collect a small fold for subsequent stretching and begin smoothly stretching of the F2 muscle. Hold the stretching for 5-15 seconds when you reach the attachment points of F2.</p><p><strong>3 step.</strong> Soothing the skin<br>The top layers of the skin may look crumpled for a short time after such intense pressure and stretch marks. Let&#39;s help them find their rightful place as quickly as possible.<br>Using these light massage movements, you bring the skin back to the place where it is supposed to be. Pay attention to your sensations. After the first times you perform this massage, your muscle may ache a little, this is absolutely normal.</p><p>Do the same on the other side!</p><p>One more step towards natural rejuvenation has been taken!<br><br>Good luck!&nbsp;<span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f917.svg);\">&nbsp;</span><br>Alex</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
