                        "id": "fcddbda5-8042-4b50-aada-01c6c3405cde",
                        "exerciseName": "Frictions F1",
                        "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Frictions of F1 levator.</strong></p><p>Now you are ready to meet an advanced, very powerful and effective massage for the midface. We will deeply work out the F1, and later F2 levators muscles with frictions. See the picture for the attachment points of these muscles.</p><p>Thanks to this technique:<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; the nasolabial folds will decrease or completely disappear,<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; the skin rolls in the cheekbones will decrease, which let the cheekbones to look cleaner and younger,<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; the groove on the eyelid-cheek border is erased or becomes less noticeable,<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; the problem of the sagging lower eyelid is improved.</p><p><strong>Attention!</strong><br>In this technique, it is very important to work with the muscles. Most likely it will not be easy to find them at the first time, but it is necessary to do. Spend some time studying these small but such important muscles for your youthful look. Touch your face with your fingers, smile, wiggle your nose - this way you will find your F1 and F2 muscles faster. Check the picture for its position and attachment points.<br>Also remember that the skin under the eyes is very delicate, do not pull your eyelids down during the procedure.</p><p><strong>Technique:</strong><br><strong>1 step</strong>. Fix F1 with index finger and rub.<br>One finger will be fixing, and the other will be working.<br>To begin with, place the fixing finger under the periosteum (the bone of the orbit of the eye from below) so that the fingertip on the index finger rests tightly against the nose, it will not be necessary to lift it higher. The fixing finger protects the delicate skin of the eyes from strain.<br>Start rubbing the F1.</p><p>It is <strong>IMPORTANT</strong> to rub the muscle deep in the tissues,<strong>&nbsp;t</strong><strong>he frequency of friction is low</strong>.<br><strong>2 step</strong>. Stretching.<br>After frictions, you need to stretch the muscles well. To do this, the fixing finger stays at the same position pressing tightly at upper attachment of F1. Place the fingertip of the working finger on F1, next to the fixing fingertip and press tightly in. Keeping the pressure shift the fingertip down a bit. Reposition the fixing fingertip next to the working one and fix F1 again. Keeping the pressure shift the fingertip down a bit again. Repeat the sequence again if the working fingertip have not reach the F1 base.</p><p>Look in the picture where lips levators begin and end. F1 is a little longer than F2 and can be stretched with 2-3 dotted stretch marks.</p><p><br></p><p>Repeat the technique in the same way on the other side. One careful approach on each side is enough.</p><p>How does it feel? Did you work with the muscles deeply?</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
