                        "id": "74ee3cb9-41d4-412d-accf-7229c6ad2835",
                        "exerciseName": "Frictions F2",
                        "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Frictions of F2 levator.</strong></p><p>We continue working on F2 levators muscles with frictions, relaxing and stretching them. Check the picture for the attachment points of these muscles.<br>Thanks to this technique:<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; the nasolabial folds will decrease or completely disappear,<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; the skin rolls in the cheekbones will decrease, which let the cheekbones to look clearer and younger,<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; the groove on the eyelid-cheek border is erased or becomes less noticeable,<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; the problem of the sagging lower eyelid is improved.</p><p><strong>Attention!</strong><br>In this technique, it is very important to work with the muscles. Most likely it will not be easy to find them at the first time, but it is necessary to do. Spend some time studying these small but such important muscles for your youthful look. Touch your face with your fingers, smile, wiggle your nose - this way you will find your F1 and F2 muscles faster. Check the picture for their positions and attachment points.<br>Do not neglect the fact that the skin under the eyes is very delicate, do not pull your eyelids down during the procedure.</p><p><span class=\"fr-video fr-deletable fr-fvc fr-dvb fr-draggable\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"true\"><iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/608061753\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\" class=\"fr-draggable\"></iframe></span><br></p><p><strong>Technique:</strong><br><strong>1 step</strong>. Fix F2 with index finger.<br>One finger will be fixing, and the other will be working.<br>To begin with, place the fixing finger, the same way as for F1 frictions, under the periosteum (the bone of the orbit of the eye from below) so that the fingertip on the index finger rests tightly against the nose, it will not be necessary to lift it higher. The fixing finger protects the delicate skin of the eyes from strains.</p><p><strong>2 step.</strong> Frictions of F2.<br>Place the working finger along the nasolabial fold, with the fingertip slightly touching the wing of nose. Press in and hold for couple of seconds<br>then push the soft tissues up towards the fixing finger. Start slow rubbing movements. Do frictions for 20-30 seconds.<br>It is IMPORTANT to rub the muscle deep in the tissues, the frequency of frictions is low. If the fold of soft tissues become thin and the F2 muscle slips out of it - collect it again.</p><p><strong>3 step.</strong> Stretching.<br>After frictions, you need to stretch the muscles well. To do this, press the beginning of F2 with the fixing fingertip tightly. Place the working fingertip right under the fixing one and press it in tightly then slowly pull the pressed soft tissues down a bit. Keep pressure. If the working fingertip have not yet reached the nasolabial fold, reposition the fixing fingertip on just stretched part of F2 and fix it next to the working fingertip. Again, with working fingertip press in and pull the soft tissues down stretching the F2. Stop when you reach the nasolabial fold.</p><p>Repeat the technique in the same way on the other side. One careful approach on each side is enough.<br>How does it feel?<br>Did you work with the muscles deeply?</p><p>Good luck!&nbsp;<span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f917.svg);\">&nbsp;</span><br>Alex</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
