                        "id": "601cde6f-ba93-4d53-ad18-fea92e1fc5ca",
                        "exerciseName": "SM of the forehead",
                        "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Sculpting massage of the forehead</strong></p><p>Do not apply sculptural massage on a clean skin! Use a small amount of OIL, aloe-vera gel, or another massage product.<br>Place a few drops on your palms, rub them, and place your palms on your face.<br>You must achieve a gliding movement without losing the grip of your palms.<br>You need to work the tissues of your face out deeply and not just stroke your face.</p><p>Check out what muscles you will work on</p><p><span class=\"fr-video fr-deletable fr-fvc fr-dvb fr-draggable\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"true\"><iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/543673424\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\" class=\"fr-draggable\"></iframe></span><br></p><p><strong>Caution:&nbsp;</strong>You don&rsquo;t need to compensate the motion by straining your neck.</p><p><strong>Technique</strong><br><strong>Set 1</strong>.<br>- Put your elbows on the table.<br>- Connect the edges of the palms and place your forehead firmly on the palms so the bases of your palms would be just above the eyebrows. The goal is to achieve an adhesion of tissues and shift the tissues of the forehead upwards.<br>- Provide the relaxation of the neck and the pressure on the tissues. Pause for 20 seconds.<br>- Straighten up fingers of connected palms, allow the head to fall under its own weight compensating the pressure by your hands. After that, let the head slide slowly downwards over the base of your palms.<br>- Keep your neck as relaxed as possible without losing the pressure on the tissues.<br>- Do not force the sliding to make it faster. The slower it goes the better effect you get.</p><p>Stop sliding when the base of your palms reaches the line of the hair grow.</p><p>Place your forehead on the starting position and repeat sliding without pause twice.</p><p><strong>Set 2</strong><br>Do the same exercise but with the palms moved left so that the right palm will be placed above the left eyebrow.</p><p>The first sliding with a 20 seconds pause, the second and the third without.</p><p><strong>Set 3</strong><br>Do the same exercise with the palms moved to the right so that the left palm will be placed above your right eyebrow. Mind the pause.</p><p>Move on to the Sculptural Massage of the middle part of the face.</p><p><br></p><p><em>See you soon <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60c.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
