                        "id": "6d5f80a3-865d-4c47-b8ed-aa853254c6d3",
                        "exerciseName": "SM of the middle part of the face",
                        "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Sculpting massage of the middle part of the face‚†Ä</strong></p><p>! This exercise is performed NOT on clean skin. You&rsquo;ll need OIL, aloe-vera gel, or another massage product.<br>Put a few drops on your palms, rub them, and place your palms on your face.<br>It is important to glide without losing the grip of your palms on the skin.<br>You need to work out the tissues of your face deeply, and not just stroke your face.</p><p>Check out what muscles you will work on</p><p><span class=\"fr-video fr-deletable fr-fvc fr-dvb fr-draggable fr-active\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"true\"><iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/543673483\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\" class=\"fr-draggable\"></iframe></span><br></p><p><strong>Caution:</strong> Relax your neck. Use the weight of your head for the natural pressure.<br>‚†Ä<br><strong>Technique</strong><br><strong>1 set</strong>. Cheekbones<br>- Place elbows on the table.<br>- Place the base of the palms next to the nose, so that the cheekbones would rest in the middle of each palm, fingers relaxed and slightly touching the ears. Get a good grip on the tissues.<br>- Relax your neck and put some pressure on the tissues - allow your head rest under its own weight on your hands. Hold this position for 20 seconds.<br>- Change the tilt angle of the palms , straiten the fingers &nbsp;and let your head slide over the palms. Keep your neck as relaxed as possible without losing the pressure on the tissue.</p><p>- Repeat the gliding action twice without pause.</p><p><strong>2 set</strong>. Cheeks<br>When you sculpturing the cheeks place the palms just below the cheekbones. Do same actions. First pressure and pause for 20 seconds, then slide until the line of the hair grow, repeat sliding twice without pause.</p><p>Repeat the sequence for the other side.</p><p><strong>Attention!</strong><br>Try to slide slowly. The slower you slide, the higher the intensity.</p><p>Now let&rsquo;s move on to the lower part of your face.</p><p><br>See you soon. <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60c.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
