                        "id": "a0728b63-44a3-4245-84f3-ad723f591fcf",
                        "exerciseName": "VM of the mid face",
                        "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Vacuum massage for middle face</strong></p><p>Renewed skin with only the power of a small silicone cup!<br>The vacuum massage (VM) affects the secretion of collagen and elastin:<br>- skin gets rid of toxins and looks fresher;<br>- bags and dark circles under eyes disappear;<br>- pores shrink;<br>- wrinkles get smoothed.</p><p><strong>Caution:&nbsp;</strong>Do not overdo it. After a vacuum massage (VM), the face should blush a little - this is called hyperemia. This is what we are trying to achieve. Light hyperemia will disappear within half a day, in a day at the very latest. However, if you &quot;work too hard&quot;, it may stay for several days. Be careful, this is your face after all!</p><p>There are contraindications to a vacuum massage:<br>- acute diseases and flare-up of chronic conditions;<br>- skin defects;<br>- thrombophlebitis (vein inflammation);<br>- increased fragility and vascular permeability (disrupted blood supply to soft tissues);<br>- severe cardiovascular disease (severe disease involving heart or blood vessels);<br>- mental disorders; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <br>- age over 80.</p><p><strong>Technique</strong><br>- You need oil to perform this massage technique (see the oil guide). Use a silicon cup with a diameter of about 1 inch (2.5-3 cm). Put a few drops on your palms, rub them, and place your palms on your face. You can also add some oil on the cup&#39;s base directly for better gliding. ‚†Ä<br>- No need to create a strong vacuum!<br><strong>1. Action</strong> - suction.<br>- Create a vacuum with a cup so that the cup sticks well to your skin and leave it for 5-10 seconds there. Start the VM of the middle face from the area next to your nose, then move on to the next place toward your ear and repeat the action.<br><strong>2. Action</strong> - circular movements.<br>- Press the squeezed cup to your skin creating the vacuum. The cup should be able to move without losing the vacuum &ndash; this is exactly what you need. 2 to 3 circular movements on one spot, then you can move on to the next part of your face and repeat the action.<br>- In the middle face, the skin is more flexible than on the forehead, so that the circular movements should be done more careful! If in doubt, skip the action 2 and go straight to the action 3.<br><strong>3. Action</strong> - horizontal movements.<br>- Press the squeezed cup to your skin creating the vacuum and drag the cup horizontally from the nose to your ear and slightly upward. If the cup has lost the vacuum, create it again and continue from the same place.<br>- Working on the middle face, you can only perform horizontal motions from nose to ear.<br>- The time you spend on every area is very individual and depends on the sensitivity of your skin, on how much vacuum you created and so on. Perform the massage until your skin is slightly red. No more and no less.</p><p><strong>Important!‚†Ä</strong><br>Make sure to wash off the oil or other massage product afterwards! Don&#39;t leave it on your skin.<br>During the vacuum massage, the skin releases many substances that will not have a beneficial effect on it! These substances must be removed from the skin, otherwise it can result in irritation, redness or skin peeling off.<br>Make sure that the vacuum you create is minimal! <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60e.svg);\">&nbsp;</span><br>Do not try to pull too much skin into the cup.</p><p><em>Listen to your sensations,&nbsp;</em><br><em>See you in a bit! <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f609.svg);\">&nbsp;</span> &nbsp;</em></p><p>Move on to the VM for lower face.</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
