        "dayDate": "02/21/2026",
        "description": "<p>Hey –ê–ª–µ–∫—Å–µ–π ! <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f917.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p><p>Great to see you in the first day of power up course + Advanced For Mouth and Jaw!<span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f44f.svg);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p>After this power-up course you are going to have the checklist with daily rejuvenating exercises from basic Look Younger course enriched with new 13 advanced techniques to improve your mouth and jaw. Advanced massages demand more time for practicing and learning. We will take it easy and will be learning 1 or maximum 3 new techniques a day.</p><p>We will start with a deep work out on the mastication muscles group:<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span> <strong>&nbsp;Relaxation of masseters<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; Stretching pterygoids<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; Modelling of mastication muscles</strong></p><p>Spasm in mastication muscles leads to TMJ issue and entails such consequences as bruxism, teeth problems and headache. &nbsp;From esthetic point of view spasm in chewing muscles provokes shortening of bone structure of your head, and as result forms creases and wrinkles on the face. Chewing muscles are the largest on the face and impact the shape of the face in general. It is hard to see direct impact of the relaxation of this group but in the long run rejuvenation training it is highly important to keep them relaxed together with other facial muscles. It is essential for deeper relaxation of the whole face in order to treat bothering wrinkles effectively.</p><p>Recommended flow:<br>1. Keep doing morning exercises as usually.<br>2. Check out new exercises.<br>3. Practice your set of already learned exercises.<br>4. Practice new ones.</p><p>Do not worry if you miss a day of study. You can always catch up. New exercises will be added to your Plan For Today, you will not miss them.</p><p>Good luck! üôÇ</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\"> <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"\"></a></p>",
