                        "id": "3983aa1c-8c77-46c4-9aa4-1037b8c2d353",
                        "exerciseName": "Spinal traction",
                        "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Spinal traction, shoulder opening</strong></p><p>Easy and effective exercise for opening the shoulders.<br>- Shoulders get more mobility.<br>- Chest is open, bringing relief to the chest-shoulders area.</p><p><strong>Caution:</strong> Use the natural weight of your body. Do not push!</p><p><strong>Technique</strong><br>- Step up to a clean wall, place your hands with the outstretched arms on the wall at the forehead-level slightly wider than your shoulder.<br>- Take a step back while keeping the hands in the same place.<br>- Let your upper body bend down, feel the stretching in your chest and shoulder muscles (deltoid and pectoralis).<br>- Breath evenly. Stay in this stretching position for 4 to 10 inhale-exhale rounds.<br>- Return to the upright position and feel the difference, try to rotate your arms, stretch them upwards.</p><p><strong>Attention!</strong><br>If your shoulders are already flexible enough and your head (provided keeping a straight spine line) goes lower than your shoulders, the stretching should be performed as follows: the crown towards the wall&hellip; Well if you are that flexible, you surely already know how to do it.&nbsp;<span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f44d.svg);\">&nbsp;</span> <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f609.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Relax, and take it easy!</em> &nbsp;<span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60c.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
