                        "id": "fa3d83bc-ae8f-4f6b-84dc-6cce8e52aae0",
                        "exerciseName": "Temple lifting",
                        "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Temple lift, eyes opener</strong></p><p>One of the most important techniques for facial rejuvenation. A facelift in just 30 seconds is possible in almost any situation.&nbsp;</p><p><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; The upper eyelids are naturally lifted;<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; The corners of the eyes are raised;<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; The nasolabial folds are reduced.</p><p>The technique is simple, all you need is your hands for supporting your face and 30-40 seconds of your time. The lifting effect will be visible immediately.&nbsp;</p><p>It surely will not last long after the first time, but if you keep on doing it every day, the effect will last longer with every day. The temporal region affects the appearance of the entire face, not only the eyes and forehead. So, it needs to be included into your daily routine, and as a result you will have a facelift effect without any surgery. Not kidding, practice well and see for yourself. &nbsp;<span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f44c.svg);\">&nbsp;</span> <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f609.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Caution:&nbsp;</strong>You tighten the temples, not the eyes. So, please do not touch the skin around the eyes, it is very delicate.</p><p><span class=\"fr-video fr-deletable fr-fvc fr-dvb fr-draggable\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"true\"><iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/542666094\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\" class=\"fr-draggable\"></iframe></span><br></p><p><strong>Technique</strong><br>- You need your both hands for this exercise. Place the base of your palms on the temples so that you do not touch the eyelids, the fingers are pointing to the crown.<br>- You slightly pull in your palms into the temples for 3 to 5 seconds. Place your elbows on the table, the head fixed between your hands, and relax your neck.<br>- As soon as you relax your neck, the head will naturally slide down under its own weight. Adjust the pressure with your palms so that your head slides down VERY slowly. This motion is over when the fingers meet at the crown. The way is short, so take your time. The slower you let your head slide, the better is the effect. 30 to 40 seconds should be enough for this motion.</p><p><strong>Attention!</strong><br>Be sure not to stretch your skin around your eyes. You work with the muscles of the temporal region on the deep level, not with the skin. The skin will tighten all by itself as the soft tissues under the skin improve.</p><p>From my personal experience, I can say that this is the fastest way to refresh your face in almost any situation. It is very fast and effective, if you for example need to look fresher for a photo.</p><p><br></p><p><em>Take care of your pretty eyes! <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f64f.svg);\">&nbsp;</span> <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f609.svg);\">&nbsp;</span> &nbsp;</em></p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
