                        "id": "d653bff5-9718-45f8-a279-9fa8d4382b41",
                        "exerciseName": "Stretching pterygoideus",
                        "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Relaxing the deep chewing muscles.<br>The lateral pterygoideus muscles.</strong></p><p><strong>1 step</strong>. Stretching to ears.<br>We shift the jaw towards the ears stretching the lateral pterygoid muscles.<br>To do this, open your mouth and place the bases of your palms on the large chewing muscles, fingers relaxed and overlapping the ears.<br>Keep this grip and rest your elbows on the table or knees. Relax your neck, let the weight of your head do the job. Relax your jaw, this is very important, it should let a slight shift of the jaw which is stretching the lateral pterygoid muscles. You should feel the tension somewhere under the cheekbones.<br>Keep this stretching for 20-30 seconds.<br>Slowly release.</p><p><img src=\"https://facelift-service.azurewebsites.net/BeautifyManContent/Images/e4b161d0-3592-4023-8396-02a40c496890.jpg\" style=\"width: 300px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\"></p><p><strong>2 step.</strong> Stretching diagonally.<br>Do the same kind of stretching diagonally.<br>This time place the mount of Venus (the soft part of the palm under the thumb) on the large chewing muscles, fingers relaxed and touching the back of the neck below the ears.<br>Keep the grip and rest your elbows on the table or knees, Let the weight of your head do the job. Relax your jaw, this is most important here, and hold for 20-30 seconds. You should feel the tension in the same area as in the previous step.<br>Slowly release.</p><p><strong>3 step.</strong> Relax.<br>With light circular and tapping movement massage the large chewing muscles. 15-30 seconds should be enough for this.</p><p>Proceed to modelling chewing muscles.</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
