                        "id": "3928f192-12b2-47c6-9a90-8f7f43f61eee",
                        "exerciseName": "VM of the forehead",
                        "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Vacuum massage for forehead&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Renewed skin with only the power of a small silicone cup!<br>The vacuum massage (VM) affects the secretion of collagen and elastin:<br>- skin gets rid of toxins and looks fresher;<br>- bags and dark circles under eyes disappear;<br>- pores shrink;<br>- wrinkles get smoothed.</p><p><strong>Caution:</strong> Do not overdo it. After a vacuum massage (VM), the face should blush a little - this is called hyperemia. This is what we are trying to achieve. Light hyperemia will disappear within half a day, in a day at the very latest. However, if you &quot;work too hard&quot;, it may stay for several days. Be careful, this is your face after all!</p><p>There are contraindications to a vacuum massage:<br>- acute diseases and flare-up of chronic conditions;<br>- skin defects;<br>- thrombophlebitis (vein inflammation);<br>- increased fragility and vascular permeability (disrupted blood supply to soft tissues);<br>- severe cardiovascular disease (severe disease involving heart or blood vessels);<br>- mental disorders;<br>- age over 80.</p><p><strong>Technique</strong><br>- You need oil to perform this massage technique (see the oil guide). Use a silicon cup with a diameter of about 1 inch (2.5-3 cm). Put a few drops on your palms, rub them, and place your palms on your face. Also add some oil on the cup&#39;s working surface directly for better gliding. ‚†Ä<br>- No need to create a strong vacuum!<br><strong>1. Action</strong> - suction.<br>- Create a vacuum with a cup by grabbing the cup between your thumb and index finger and squeezing it. Press it to your skin and then let it go. This would create a vacuum that sticks the cup to your face by picking up the skin underneath.<br>-Leave the cup sticking to your skin for 5 to 10 seconds.<br>- Repeat this action several times on different parts of your forehead.<br><strong>2. Action</strong> - circular movements.<br>- Press the squeezed cup to your skin creating the vacuum. The cup should be able to move without losing the vacuum &ndash; this is exactly what you need. 2 to 3 circular movements on one spot, then you can move on to the next part of your forehead and repeat the action.<br><strong>3. Action</strong> - horizontal movements.<br>- Press the squeezed cup to your skin creating the vacuum and drag the cup horizontally across your forehead. If the cup has lost the vacuum, create the vacuum and continue from the same place. Vertical movements are also possible.</p><p>- The time you spend on every area is very individual and depends on the sensitivity of your skin, on how much vacuum you created and so on. Perform the massage until your skin is slightly red. No more and no less.</p><p><strong>Important !‚†Ä</strong><br>Make sure to wash off the oil or other massage product afterwards! Don&#39;t leave it on your skin.<br>During the vacuum massage, the skin releases many substances that will not have a beneficial effect on it! These substances must be removed from the skin, otherwise it can result in irritation, redness or skin peeling off.<br>Make sure that the vacuum you create is minimal!<br>Do not try to pull too much skin into the cup.</p><p><br></p><p><em>Be gentle with yourself,</em><br><em>Good luck! <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60c.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</em></p><p><br></p><p>Move on to the VM for middle face.</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
