                        "id": "9162a4c3-030f-46df-8813-932a1272ffb2",
                        "exerciseName": "On the roller",
                        "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Laying on the roller</strong></p><p>Unique, easy, relaxing and super effective exercise to release spasms in your spine inner muscles and improve neck static. &nbsp;Look at the picture, look at the muscles supporting the spine from outside and inside (long muscle of the neck, lat. &quot;longus colli&quot;) of the spine bone, they connect vertebrae one to others. What? Do you think happens, when they get into spasmodic state? They cement the curves of the spine that actually we need to straighten for the sake of better wellbeing and rejuvenation.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>We can&#39;t reach the anterior surface of the spine with hands to massage them. These inner muscles can be relaxed only by prolonged stretching, not shorter than 5 minutes. Even in yoga, you will not find the poses that can help their relaxation effectively. Only laying on the rolls can really help in relaxing inner spine muscles to improve the situation around 7th cervical vertebra, which normally sticks out with ageing.&nbsp;</p><p>Technique is simple, but there are precautions:<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;It is not for pregnant<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; Coming out of this exercise should be VERY slow and delicate because you stretch your spine, so fast jump out from the pose can cause lumbago.<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; You may &nbsp;fall asleep in this pose. This is OK. Just come out of it even slower.</p><p><strong>Technique</strong><br>1. Make roll from a bath towel. Fold it twice along its length, roll and tie it up with a ribbon. You can adjust thickness and hardness of the roll according to your need by softening or tightening the ribbon. For the beginning, start with loosen ribbon.</p><p>2. Prepare the place on the flat solid surface like a floor, make sure that you get no wind over there. Use yoga mat or a rag to lay on.</p><p><strong>1 action.</strong> Under the lower back. 5-10 minutes.<br>Sit with the crossed legs, place the roll under the lower back perpendicular to it. Lay down on the mat, straiten your legs and relax. Heels are at the same width as your shoulders, arms stretched out over your head. Relax and breathe evenly. Relax in this pose for 5-10 minutes.<br>To make the stretching deeper, connect your big toes, keeping the heels on the same spots, and put your palms on the floor over your head with elbows pointing upwards.</p><p><strong>IMPORTANT.</strong> Coming out of the pose is very slow. First, turn your body on the side and pull out the roll from the lower back. If you finished the exercise, slowly get onto your hands and knees and do simple bands of the spine, then slowly get up on the feet.</p><p><strong>2 action.</strong> Under the middle of the back. 5-10 minutes.</p><p>From the previous action pose turn on your side and adjust the roll higher, to the middle of the back, again perpendicular to the spine, and again lay on it and relax. &nbsp;For deeper stretching, do the same toes connection and palms set on floor. Relax for 5-10 minutes.<br><strong>IMPORTANT.</strong> Coming out of the pose is very slow.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>3 action</strong>. Under the shoulder blades perpendicular. 5-10 minutes.</p><p>From the previous action pose turn on your side and adjust the roll higher, under the shoulder blades, again perpendicular to the spine, and again lay on it and relax. &nbsp;For deeper stretching, do the same toes connection and palms set on floor. Relax for 5-10 minutes.<br><strong>IMPORTANT.</strong> Coming out of the pose is very slow.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>4 action.</strong> Between the shoulder blades, along the spine. 5-10 minutes.</p><p>From the previous action pose turn on your side and change orientation of the roll, this time set it along the spine, between your shoulder blades. One end of the roll should be at the 7th cervical vertebra area, so that the cervical vertebrae and head would be lower than the rest of the spine resting on the roll. Relax on the roll. &nbsp;</p><p>For deeper stretching relaxation of the inner spine muscles, do few swings of arms in opposite directions. One arm along the body, the other is stretched straight over your head, change their positions. Try to do 10 swings like this, then relax for 5-10 minutes. Do the same toes connection and palms set on floor for deeper stretching if you fell like it.</p><p><strong>IMPORTANT.</strong> Coming out of the pose is very slow. First, turn your body on the side. Slowly get on all fours and do simple backbends, then slowly get to your feet.</p><p>Relaxation on the roll should be very deep, you may get sleepy easily. Do not let yourself fall asleep, especially when you just start practising this technique.</p><p><strong>Feeling sleepy?</strong> Make a couple of deep breaths and turn on your side, remove the roll from under your body and enjoy pleasant relaxation in your back. Always keep in mind that you have relaxed your spine very well, vertebrae got to forgotten positions and got stretched out from each other a bit, restructuring to the healthier spine state. This healthy state of spine got forgotten by the tissues surrounding your vertebrae. If you return very fast to the regular vertical position, some little tissues may get clamped by vertebrae just a bit. This bit can cause a giant pain, so be careful when you get up. When you do it slowly, with awareness, all the tissues will find their righteous places, and you will feel just great!</p><p><br></p><p>Love your spine and live long happy life! <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f609.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
