                "id": "0d9e8c92-68bf-470d-a031-2d444a995fa6",
                "exerciseName": "Basic neck stretching",
                "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Basic neck stretch exercise</strong></p><p>This is an excellent neck exercise that can be done anytime. Have a moment? - Stretch your neck. In this case we use this exercise as a test to determine if you are ready for the next more advanced neck exercises. Please do it gently, carefully and listen to your sensations. The neck can almost always stretch but returning to the starting position can be difficult if the neck isn&rsquo;t ready. Stretch it slowly and listen to the sensations in your neck.</p><p><strong>Caution:&nbsp;</strong>When we say &ldquo;slowly&rdquo;, we mean it! <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60e.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; A sudden moving back from a stretched state can bring an unpleasant surprise such as pain or discomfort for those with an untrained neck.</p><p>Benefits of neck stretching:<br>- Tension in the neck muscles is reduced;<br>- Head/ neck posture is corrected;<br>- Double chin starts to shrink;<br>- The shape of the face is improved;<br>- Neck wrinkles are reduced;<br>- The skin on the neck is tightened.</p><p><strong>Technique</strong><br>- Stand up straight and stretch out your neck pulling the head upwards.<br>- Turn your head to the one side until you can&rsquo;t go any further, hold it for 2 inhale-exhale-rounds, slowly return your head to its original position. Repeat the sequence for the other side.<br>- Tilt your head to one side until you can&rsquo;t go any further, hold it for 2 inhale-exhale-rounds, slowly return the head to its original position. Then repeat the sequence for the other side.<br>- Very slowly and carefully move your lower jaw forward, do not overdo it. Without delay, slowly return the head to its original position.<br>- Pull the lower jaw backwards. And then stretch it upwards without throwing your head back. Keep pulling the lower jaw upwards, breathe evenly, deeply and hold it for 2 inhale-exhale-rounds. Then slowly return the head to its original position.</p><p>You can do this exercise several times a day, if you feel like it. Don&rsquo;t forget to do it slowly and carefully every time.</p><p>If you do this exercise, it feels good and you don&rsquo;t experience any sharp pain or discomfort, then you are ready for more advanced exercises that we will learn the following days.</p><p>If you suddenly feel discomfort or sharp pain, please stop practicing and listen to the sensations. Try to do small-amplitude head rotations at first. Does it work? Very well, perform these rotations, followed by very gently stretching motions until the discomfort in the neck goes away. Then you can move on to learning the more advanced stretches.</p><p>Sharp pain doesn&rsquo;t allow you to move freely? ... &nbsp;Well, in this case, stop practicing all the neck exercises and go see your physician.</p><p><em>Be gentle to yourselves, take care!</em> <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f64f.svg);\">&nbsp;</span> <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60c.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
