                "id": "f791c2e3-84dc-4809-8287-e56311c58753",
                "exerciseName": "Smoothing of frown lines",
                "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Relieve tension in the middle of the forehead and between the eyebrows</strong></p><p>Check out the muscles we will work on</p><p>Now is the time to start smoothing your frown lines! <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60e.svg);\">&nbsp;</span><br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; Tension in the middle of the forehead is released.<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; Nose bridge tissues are returning to their original place (myofascial soft tissue correction).<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; Frowning is getting gradually out of the habit.<br><span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f449.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; Headaches caused by nervous tension are relieved.</p><p><strong>Caution:</strong> This technique is very effective and easy to learn. In this exercise, you learn how to work with your fingers deep and slow. When we say &quot;slow,&quot; it really means slow, about one millimetre in 5 seconds.</p><p><strong>Technique</strong><br>- Place your elbows on a table. Let the weight of your head lean the hooks. The back of your neck should be relaxed.<br>- Form your index fingers to &ldquo;hooks&rdquo;. Place both fingers on the nose bridge and push deep down to the bone. Feel the tissues for 10 to 20 seconds.<br>- One &ldquo;hook&rdquo; is the fixing one, you don&#39;t move it. The other one is the working one, you do move it, but very slowly, from the middle of your forehead towards the middle of your eyebrow.<br>- Return the &ldquo;hook&rdquo; to the start position. Repeat the action for the other side.<br>- Place the &ldquo;hooks&rdquo; a bit higher than your nose bridge. Now you can put them side by side with the finger joints touching each other. Push them in to the bone and keep them like this for 10 to 20 seconds. Compare your sensations to the previous position.<br>- Repeat the same slow movements using your working &ldquo;hooks&rdquo; for about 1 inch (2.5 centimetres)<br>- Place your &ldquo;finger hooks&rdquo; further up again. You may need to do it several times before you reach the hairline. Repeat the action.<br>- Going over the hairline is OK, it is even appreciated.<span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f44d.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Attention!&nbsp;</strong><br>The movements of the working finger should be deep and slow, but not too long. The fixing finger should not drop the pressure while the working finger is moving.</p><p>How did it go? Can you feel the relief already?</p><p><em>Take it easy! <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60c.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</em></p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
