                "id": "0d61698e-365e-4b7e-9d50-0bdb39a98c73",
                "exerciseName": "Massage for the circular muscle of the eye",
                "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Massage for the circular muscle of the eye</strong></p><p>Eyes, eyes, eyes, let&#39;s help them!</p><p>Benefits of the exercise:<br>- Lymph drainage of the eye zone.<br>- Dark circles under the eyes and baggy lower eyelids are improved.<br>- Crow&rsquo;s feet wrinkles decrease.<br>- Elasticity of the eyelids is increased.<br>- First treatment for the lower eyelid-cheek junction deformations.</p><p><strong>Caution:&nbsp;</strong>The eye area has the most sensitive skin on our face. It can easily get harmed. Please remember in this exercise about the one-year-old baby power rule. Working on the eye area, imagine how gently a baby would touch the face, use the same power.</p><p>Check out what muscle you will work on</p><p><span class=\"fr-video fr-deletable fr-fvc fr-dvb fr-draggable\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"true\"><iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/543693547\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\" class=\"fr-draggable\"></iframe></span><br></p><p><strong>Technique</strong><br><strong>1st step</strong>. Warm-up<br>- Use all your fingertips for this warm-up technique. Perform a massage on the whole lower eyelid area, slightly pressing in the infraorbital margin* bones. 30 seconds would be enough for the warm-up.<br><strong>2nd step</strong>. Frictions of lower eyelid<br>- Use your both index fingers. Make a little vertical fold of the soft tissues of the lid-cheek junction. You can grab about half an inch (1-1,5 cm) of soft tissues of the lower eyelid and below it, but please, do not squeeze it!<br>- Perform the massage on the fold, doing frictions very patiently and carefully. Take your time.<br>- When the fold slips out during the friction, make another fold in the next area, moving towards the end of the eye socket. Perform the same friction technique patiently. Work your way through the whole area. You can make up to 10 folds on each side, if you want to work the whole way through the eye area thoroughly and patiently. It is up to you. Listen to your sensations and the way your soft tissues respond, but do not overdo it.<br><strong>3d step</strong>. Frictions of temples<br>- When you are done with working on the lower eyelid, move to the temple area. Work on your smile lines. Take a fold next to the corner of the eye and perform the friction massage of it. The skin in this area is less sensitive, so you can apply slightly more power for the friction massage.<br>- Work your way through the whole temple area by taking the next fold and moving closer to your hairline. You may need to make 3 to 5 folds in this area.<br><strong>4th step</strong>. Stretch the wrinkles on the temples<br>- Use both hands for this technique. Both index and middle fingers are working here. Place them on the temple next to the end of the eye, where the skin is less sensitive than on the eyelids, one hand from above over your head and the other from below. The fingertips must meet before you start with the action.<br>- Push into the bone and hold it for 5 seconds, then pull both hands apart from each other for about an inch (2-2,5 cm) stretching the underlying tissues.<br>- Place the hands closer&nbsp;to the hairline and perform the same stretching technique. You may need to do it up to 4 times before you reach the hairline. Repeat the action. Going over the hairline is OK, it is even appreciated.</p><p>Repeat steps 2,3 and 4 on the other side.</p><p><strong>Attention!</strong><br>! The skin of the eye area is very sensitive. If you experience some discomfort or skin redness, reduce the power considerably.<br>! If you notice, the wrinkles of the eye area would become more definite, skip steps 2 and 3. Try it next week with reduced power.</p><p><em>Keep calm, be patient. <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f64f.svg);\">&nbsp;</span> <br>Good luck! <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60c.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</em></p><p><br></p><p>*The infraorbital margin is the lower margin of the eye socket.</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
