                "id": "79360171-ac0c-4576-99e4-5793d3430a2f",
                "exerciseName": "Frictions",
                "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Frictions on middle part of the face</strong></p><p>That is a great exercise!<br>Very soon you&rsquo;ll feel how effectively this exercise works on the facial tissues. <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f609.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Caution:&nbsp;</strong>This technique is very intensive. So, please, don&rsquo;t overdo it! Otherwise, you can get a tissue inflammation. You know, they say &ldquo;Give a fool rope enough&hellip;&rdquo; <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f605.svg);\">&nbsp;</span><br>Work with your face delicately, please. Just imagine how a one-year-old baby would be touching, pushing, pinching your face with its maximum power. You should not do it harder than that.</p><p><strong>Benefits:</strong><br>- <strong>Full face</strong>, puffy tissues and visibly uneven skin: the friction technique reduces the fat deposits under your facial skin making it firm and smooth;<br>- <strong>Skinny face</strong>: frictions help to revitalize the fat cells of your stored fat reserve, providing the necessary nutrition to accelerate the metabolism, and as a result, your fat deposits under the skin will recover!</p><p><strong>Technique</strong><br>- You need your both index fingers for this action. The first one is for fixing and should not be moved. The second one is the working finger and will perform the main action.<br>- Place your fixing finger on the center part of your cheek, so that the fingertip would point to the middle of your eye, and its beginning would rest in the middle of the jawline.<br>- Place your working finger in parallel to the fixing one near the nose (the middle joint of your finger would touch the alar wing of the nose).<br>- Move the working finger to the fixing one, folding your tissues. You should try to pick up as many tissues as you can. Your fold can be bigger or smaller than the one on the video. This is absolutely normal! We all have different fat deposits under the skin, different liquid levels, different qualities of soft-tissues.<br>- Start moving your working finger slightly up and down keeping the fold firmly. Little by little the tissues would escape from your fold as a result of your frictions. If it slips out too fast, return to the folding again. Don&lsquo;t do the frictions more than twice on the same spot.<br>- Move your fixing finger toward the ear with the distance of 1 to 2 times bigger than your finger. The working finger starts moving from the place where the previous fold has slipped out. Do the same foldings and frictions as previously. Then move the fixing finger again like you did before and repeat the frictions.<br>- You can do 3 to 4 foldings on each cheek. It is not necessary to do more than 4.</p><p>- Repeat the sequence on the other side of your face.</p><p>- There is another variation. If your fingers are tired you can straighten your palm and use it instead repeating the sequence&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Attention!</strong></p><p>! Frictions should be done on CLEAN skin only! If you put on some oil or creme, your skin is going to be SO slippery! You won&rsquo;t be able to hold your skin folded and work with it properly<br>Remember, in this case, &ldquo;harder&rdquo; doesn&rsquo;t mean &ldquo;better&rdquo;. &nbsp;Please, don&rsquo;t squeeze the tissues between your fingers for dear life!&nbsp;</p><p>! <strong>Skinny face</strong>: If you get a tired look after the frictions - stop practicing it and let your skin recover. Then start doing it again with half of the power and once in 3 days.</p><p>DO NOT THINK IT IS NOT YOUR CASE! <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60e.svg);\">&nbsp;</span><br>I have made this exact mistake... until my loved ones would start noticing it. Well, recovery took some time, but everything is good after all. Remember the one-year-old kid touch rule and resume practicing 1 to 2 times a week.</p><p><em>Take it easy!&nbsp;<span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60c.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</em></p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\"> <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"\"></a></p>",
