                "id": "b9036147-b589-4234-bad7-4a991d5ee358",
                "exerciseName": "Smoothing the mandible",
                "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Smoothing the lower jawline</strong></p><p>Time to get rid of unevenness and sagging cheeks!<br>Many muscles are crossing and building the jawline. Ideally, the jawline should be even and smooth. Unfortunately, it is not always like this. As we get older, it feels rather like a washboard. Any dysfunction of the jaw muscles can result in unevenness, bumps and sagging cheeks.<br>Good news! &nbsp;<span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f64c.svg);\">&nbsp;</span> This amazing technique can help you with it. Surely, the more you practice, the more results you see.</p><p><strong>Caution:</strong> This exercise can be performed without any oils. You&rsquo;ll see, you won&rsquo;t stretch your skin. Don&rsquo;t worry. Still worrying? <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60a.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; Then use a bit of oil for your hands.<br>As for men... man, you&#39;d better shave your face before doing the exercise. <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60e.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p><p>Check out what muscles you will work on</p><p><span class=\"fr-video fr-deletable fr-fvc fr-dvb fr-draggable\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"true\"><iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/543709931\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\" class=\"fr-draggable\"></iframe></span><br></p><p><strong>Technique</strong><br>- For this exercise, use the index finger formed to a hook that you used for the chin massage.<br>- This time the one hand is going to be the fixing hand and the other one is the working hand.<br>- Place &ldquo;the hooks&rdquo; on your chin, thumbs pressing carefully under the chin. Fix the one &ldquo;hook&rdquo; firmly to your jawline, the other one grabs the jawline firmly and starts moving towards the ear. The thumb under the chin is leading the action. It follows the jawline till the very end of it. It should pass the jaw angle and finish the action by touching the ear.<br>- When you spot a bump or any other unevenness, make a break from the exercise for a moment and give it a bit of a massage with your fingertips, then continue the smoothing action.<br>- 5 to 10 times are enough. Listen to your sensations, please. They normally give you the feeling of how many times are enough for you.</p><p>- Repeat the sequence on the other side.</p><p><strong>Attention!</strong><br>The smoothing action should be performed with a <strong>strong grab</strong> of your jawline, <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f4aa.svg);\">&nbsp;</span> <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60e.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; quite seldom I use this word. But still, keep in mind that it is your face. Don&rsquo;t overdo it, please.</p><p><em>Take care of your jaws!</em> &nbsp;<span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f60c.svg);\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
