                "id": "4b7eceb5-4333-4ed7-8001-d932da9f936b",
                "exerciseName": "Modelling of mastication muscles",
                "exerciseDescription": "<p><strong>Modelling of mastication muscles</strong></p><p>After stretching and relaxing the chewing muscles, we direct them to their physiological places.</p><p><strong>Technique:</strong></p><p>We place the pads of the upper part of the palm under the cheekbones and firmly place our palms on the warmed-up chewing muscles.</p><p>Shift the entire array of muscles to the ears, then pull it down. Keep your jaw relaxed. The offset to the ears will be minimal, but it must be indicated.</p><p>Make 3-5 of these modelling movements.</p><p><strong>Attention!&nbsp;</strong>If you do such deep work out of the chewing muscles, it will ache the next day or even right after the exercise. Do not worry, this is normal, it will go away in a day or 2.</p><p>Get your chewing muscles to relax and boost revitalisation of the whole face!</p><p>Good luck! <span class=\"fr-emoticon fr-deletable fr-emoticon-img\" style=\"background: url(https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/emojione/2.0.1/assets/svg/1f917.svg);\">&nbsp;</span> <br>Alex</p><p data-f-id=\"pbf\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;\">Powered by <a href=\"https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1\" title=\"Froala Editor\">Froala Editor</a></p>",
